body:
Hi,

With following code, iverilog (v12.0 built from git under CentOS 7.9) generates a syntax error on the line containing localparam. It would be quite useful if iverilog were to support the use of localparam in the parameter port list.

`
module foo
  #(parameter
    SIZE = 256
    localparam BITS = $clog2(SIZE)
    )
   (
    input [BITS-1:0]	 a,
    output [BITS-1:0] y
//    input [7:0]	 a,
//    output [7:0] y
    );

   assign y = a;

endmodule
`
In my search of the iverilog github issues, I didn't find anything related to this particular use of localparam. The commercial simulators on EDA Playground all seem to support this.

Thanks.
